# A diverging source of a Handle. No user-level Handle producer exists (the
# type is native-backend internal), so the body diverges. Living in its own
# module matters: the cross-module prototype carries no `_Noreturn`, so a
# caller's reference to it survives optimisation and stays a real cross-`.o`
# symbol reference — which is exactly what must resolve at link time.

#[doc("Yield a native Handle. No constructible Handle value exists, so this diverges; it only exists to source a Handle-typed argument across a module boundary.")]
pub fn get_handle() : Handle = panic("no user-constructible Handle")
